        "ratings": [
            {
                "comment": "She is very knowledgeable, but plows through the material so fast it was hard to keep up, and making me question the value of the lecture. A bit condescending, but encourages participation. Labs are definitely challenging and the class is worth 4 credits given all the time one puts into them.",
                "difficulty_rating": 4,
                "quality_rating": 3
            },
            {
                "comment": "Annemarie is a gift from above. Incredibly knowledgeable, very flexible and understanding of extenuating circumstances, and a fun professor overall. If you are interested in a career in remote sensing, international development, etc. she is a must to have as a prof.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Engaging, as modern as it gets in the field. Great opportunities and connections for research. Only real critique is disorganized. Remote sensing isn't easy no matter how you density slice it, but she does a phenomenal job teaching core concepts while giving you hands on experience as well.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Don't read the textbook, not helpful. The lab papers do take much longer to complete than the allotted lab time. Mine always ended up being 6+ pgs. So don't get caught on Thursday night trying to complete one. And for this class really know the essence of the material. She carves out key concepts for the class. And yes, her wardrobe is phenomenal!",
                "difficulty_rating": 3,
                "quality_rating": 4
            },
            {
                "comment": "The organization of lectures was slightly confusing but the professor presented the material clearly. This course covers a wide range of remote sensing applications in a short amount of time. Labs take some work outside of class. Exams were difficult but curved generously and extra credit was available.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Classroom was poorly handled. Lectures tended to be circular and handouts were worthless. Taught basics but expected you to know more specifics. Had an hour and 15 min per week for lab but each weekly lab took more like 6 hours to complete. Unprofessional dress was distracting. Make sure to double check your grade for accuracy.",
                "difficulty_rating": 5,
                "quality_rating": 2
            }
        ],
